postcontent: This is a "Standard" model Browning hi-power in 9 mm, in excellent condition, mfgd in 1992, Belgium made. Has been fired less than 50 times. Not sure why it was labeled "Standard" as it is loaded with more features than any of the other runs, has polished blue frame and slide, 2- 13 rd. magazine, ambidextrious safety, and adjustable sights. The adjustable sights are the rarest of the 3 types used in the 90's, you may look at a lot of hi-powers before you find one with this rear sight on it. The dove tail was cut farther back in the slide for this sight than the more common, lower profile sight. This one has the factory black checkered thumb rest grips along with a beautiful set of Pachmeyr wrap grips that really set it off and actually make it feel like its a part of your hand. These are actually molded together, so while they can be disassembled like the other bx-25 mags, they CANNOT be taken apart from each other. As reliable as the standard BX-1 10-round Ruger rotary magazine. Stainless steel feed lips are designed to present cartridges into the action at a 30 degree angle for better feed reliability. Stainless steel, constant force spring provides feed consistency round after round. Anti-tilt follower is injection molded from a high lubricity polyacetal for consistent reliability. BX-25 X2 magazines will work with any factory original Ruger 10/22 Rifle, SR-22 Rifle, 22 Charger Pistol and 77/22 Rifle. The BX-25 will run reliably with a wide variety of ammunition and requires no lubrication. Kel-Tec 12 Gauge KSG PUMP -Black- NEW IN BOX!

Here i have a brand new Kel-Tec 12 gauge shotgun KSG. This is Kel-Tecs first shotgun on the market. This is similar to the Kel-Tec RFB rifle in size, shape and design but the KSG ejects the shells downward instead of forward. This cool firearm weighs only 6.9 lbs and is as compact as legally possible. The overall measurement of this shotgun is 26.1", 7" high and has a 18.5" cylinder bore barrel. The internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 3" 12 gauge rounds, so a total of 6 shells per tube.

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard. The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in and a basic sling is included in the box. The soft rubber butt pad helps tame the recoil on this impressive shotgun.

This KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SKS-D takes AK mags
postcontent:
This is an SKS D model that was factory made to take AK mags, not those crappy duckbill mags. These are extremely hard to find as they were only imported from '88-'89, and when you CAN find them they're $800+... just do a quick Armslist search for SKS-D. I am selling mine for $500 because it doesn't have the original stock. The D model uses the same stock as a regular SKS,  just sometimes it had a filler piece in front of the mag well and the mag well is widened to fit the AK mags. 

The D models prefer Chinese AK mags and the gun comes with 1 Chinese mag. Also comes with the bayonet (not pictured) as well as the pin that holds the bayonet on. Also comes with a receiver scope mount and a Leapers 4x scope. The stock it is in is an ATI Dragunov stock and I'm aware it sucks, but again, that's why I'm listing this for $500 and not $800.
